President Trump delivered a speech at the opening of the Cameron LNG Export Facility in Hackberry, Louisiana. He praised the workers at the facility and celebrated the United States' energy independence and the growth of the American energy industry. He emphasized the importance of American energy production and the economic benefits it brings. The President also criticized the Green New Deal and vowed to protect American energy workers from policies that would harm the industry. He highlighted the success of American LNG exports and the impact it has on reducing the trade deficit and supporting American allies. Several workers from the facility shared their personal stories of how their jobs at Cameron LNG have positively impacted their lives. The President concluded his speech by congratulating the workers and the state of Louisiana.